b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Jasper is best suited for marketing teams, ad copy, brand voice content, campaigns, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Longshot AI, meanwhile, shines for fact checked content, SEO articles, blog posts, research heavy writing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Jasper describes itself as \"Enterprise AI marketing platform for brand-consistent content.\" Longshot AI, established in 2021, positions itself as \"AI writing tool with built-in fact-checking and citations.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Jasper** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 7). However, this does not mean Longshot AI is a poor choice — far from it. Longshot AI excels in its own right, particularly for fact checked content and SEO articles.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value 50+ templates for marketing use cases, go with Jasper. If unique fact-checking and citation features matters more to you, Longshot AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
